Designing a decentralized Association Set Provider (ASP) model
Current model relies on ASPs to define "clean funds".

Problems:
- Centralization risk
- False positives / false negatives
- Political/regulatory capture

Open questions:
- Should we use N-of-M ASP validation?
- How to weight trust between providers?
- Can we make ASPs economically accountable?

Goal: minimize trust while maintaining usability.
